<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta name="description" content="Explore the Zodiac API to find zodiac signs and their date ranges. Access API documentation and more.">
  <meta name="author" content="Your Name or Company">
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow">
  <title>Zodiac API Documentation</title>

  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
  <%= csp_meta_tag %>

  <!-- Link to favicon -->
  <link rel="icon" href="<%= asset_path('favicon.ico') %>" type="image/x-icon">

  <!-- Stylesheets -->
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>

  <!-- JavaScripts -->
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
</head>
<body>
  <header style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 20px;">
    <img src="<%= asset_path('logo.png') %>" alt="Zodiac API Logo" style="width: 200px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
    <h1>API Documentation</h1>
  </header>

  <main style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px;">
    <p>Welcome to the Zodiac API documentation! Here you can find details about available endpoints.</p>

    <h2>Endpoints</h2>

    <section style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
      <h3>Get the Zodiac Sign for the Current Date</h3>
      <pre>
GET /api/v1/current_date_zodiac_sign
      </pre>
      <p>This method returns the zodiac sign corresponding to the current date.</p>
      <p><strong>Example Response:</strong></p>
      <pre>
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Aries",
  "start_date": "2023-03-21",
  "end_date": "2023-04-19"
}
      </pre>
      <p><strong>Errors:</strong></p>
      <pre>
404: Zodiac sign not found for the current date.
      </pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
      <h3>Get the Zodiac Sign for a Specific Date</h3>
      <pre>
GET /api/v1/zodiac_sign_by_date?date=YYYY-MM-DD
      </pre>
      <p>Use this endpoint to get the zodiac sign for a user-specified date.</p>
      <p><strong>Example Response:</strong></p>
      <pre>
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Taurus",
  "start_date": "2023-04-20",
  "end_date": "2023-05-20"
}
      </pre>
      <p><strong>Errors:</strong></p>
      <pre>
400: Invalid date format. Please use the YYYY-MM-DD format.
404: Zodiac sign not found for the specified date.
      </pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
      <h3>Get the Date Range for a Zodiac Sign</h3>
      <pre>
GET /api/v1/date_range_by_sign?sign=ZodiacSign
      </pre>
      <p>This method returns the date range for the provided zodiac sign.</p>
      <p><strong>Example Response:</strong></p>
      <pre>
{
  "name": "Pisces",
  "start_date": "2023-02-19",
  "end_date": "2023-03-20"
}
      </pre>
      <p><strong>Errors:</strong></p>
      <pre>
400: The sign parameter is required.
404: Zodiac sign not found.
      </pre>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
